# Reaction time minigame
AWESOME SOURSE:[https://storyarcblog.wordpress.com/2023/02/03/a-deep-dive-look-into-fishing-minigames](https://storyarcblog.wordpress.com/2023/02/03/a-deep-dive-look-into-fishing-minigames)

![Why you all hate fishing? : r/Terraria](data:image/png;base64,)

![The Best Enchantments To Use on Fishing Rods in Minecraft](data:image/png;base64,)

This is the first "minigame" (after they choose the zone they want to fish)

1. Player aims (?) to the location they want to cast
2. They start casting, the longer the they press, the further it goes (?)
3. Lure drops in the water, wait timer start
4. They wait for a random (but not so random) time
5. Once they hear the audio or visual cure, they must react to it
6. If the reaction is done in the small timeframe, continue IF NOT jump to step 0
7. If its fish, we calculate the actual catch chance and show the promised fish. IF NOT show junk description, jump to step 0
8. The catch minigame start




# The lake zones and catching chances

Lake will have zones

In these Zones if Player tries to cast, they will have a (base location chance) to catch certain fish

Zones can have multiple fish

Fish can habit at most 2 zones (number can change for special fish)

![[Pasted image 20250803185624.png]]

On top of these (location catch) chances there will be other modifiers (exapmle; wheather, type of equipment, bait, time of the day, reaction time bonus) so it would look something like:

Final catch chance = location * wheather * rod_lvl * bait = 23%

Rod lvl chances:

	Lvl1 = 0.8
	Lvl2 = 0.85
	Lvl3 = 0.9

Blue fish has preferences:

	LIKES sunny = 100%
	DISLIKES rain = 10%

and

	LIKES gummy bear = 120%
	OK cola = 80%
	DISLIKES soup = 10%

For (pink zone, sunny, lvl3, cola)

Blue fish = 0.1 * 1 * 0.9 * 0.8 = 0.072 = 7% actual catch chance

So if our player wants to try fishing in the pink zone they would have:

- 7% of cathing Blue
- (actual catch chance) of catching Yellow
- Some chance of catching junk (nothing)

## Tiring the fish

## Left right (up down)

So these minigames have a system where we need to pull the rod in the other way fish is swimming

It creates this feeling where we are working against the fish and we need it to be weaker before we reel it

Okami (2006)

[Okami: Fishing Tutorial #kapucho #okami #tutorial #skit #fishing #gaming](https://youtu.be/aZIW-JNXM1M?feature=shared&t=141)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

" To reel you must hold your analog stick in the direction opposite of where the fish is currently swimming. Doing so will raise a line on a meter. If the line is below the green the fish will begin to distance itself from you, if it’s in the green the fish will be reeled in closer, and if the line goes into the red your fisherman friend will begin to lose health. If he loses too much health your entire fishing session will end. "

"Unlike a lot of fishing minigames, the one in Okami doesn’t encourage being precise or using specific kinds of bait to catch better fish but rather encourages repetition and spending a long amount of time in the same fishing spot. The reason for this is that the more fish you catch the larger the fish that you can see in the pond become. "

## Reeling the fish

## Button smashing

This represents the action of spinning the wheel, it is a balance between pull-but not too hard so the line doesnt break

It creates a feeling of tention, what if the line breaks?

Stardew fishing minigame

![Stardew Valley creator defends the fishing mini-game, but knows "a lot of  people really hate it" | GoNintendo](data:image/png;base64,)

It is a good representation, better than just plain button smashing, however, we can think of a better representation

- Instead of one button, we can use A -> W -> D -> S -> A -> W..... To simulate a sort of, turning feeling in the keyboard? It can be reversed in the middle to throw the player off

[HOW TO FISH IN NIER REPLICANT (REMAKE)](https://youtu.be/lHx5Hh4an4A?feature=shared&t=133)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

"Once you’ve begun luring the fish in, you must break down the fish’s health bar by mashing the circle button and holding your analog stick in a certain direction. That last part is the most important as you won’t lower the fish’s health at all if you’re pulling in the wrong direction."



On the left, we REEL the fish.

This represents the tension in the line,

if the player does it too much (or while we are pulling on the wrong dirrection too much) the line breaks, when done properly, fish become closer to player until they catch it
![[Pasted image 20250804180811.png]]

On the right, we TIRE the fish.

We can only REEL the fish while we are pulling the rod in the opposite way the fish is going

OR

After while of TIRING, fish become dormant enough to be reeled

(the green bar on the left can be increased or decreased in size according to the TIRING mini-game)
